Looking at your code, the issue with green text on dark green background appears in the quiz card and the reset all button. Here are the CSS changes you need to make to improve contrast and readability:

1. Fix the Quiz Card Text Color (Propagation Methods & Techniques Quiz)

Currently, the quiz card has dark green text on a dark green background. Change the .quiz-card styling:

```css
.quiz-card {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1e553b, #1a4a34);
  border-radius: 1.5rem;
  padding: 1.8rem;
  color: #ffffff; /* Changed from white to ensure full opacity */
  margin: 1.5rem 0;
}

/* Add this new rule for quiz card headings */
.quiz-card h3 {
  color: #ffffff !important;
  border-bottom-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.3);
}

/* Add this for quiz question text */
.quiz-question {
  background: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
  border-radius: 1rem;
  padding: 1.2rem;
  margin: 1rem 0;
  color: #ffffff;
}

/* Ensure all text in quiz card is white */
.quiz-card .quiz-question-text,
.quiz-card .quiz-option {
  color: #ffffff;
}

.quiz-card .quiz-option:hover {
  background: rgba(255,255,255,0.25);
}
```

2. Fix the Reset All Button

The reset button uses the .btn-outline class. Update its styling for better contrast:

```css
.btn-outline {
  background: transparent;
  border: 2px solid #ffffff; /* Changed from var(--primary) */
  color: #ffffff; /* Changed from var(--primary-dark) */
}

.btn-outline:hover {
  background: rgba(255,255,255,0.2);
  color: #ffffff;
  transform: translateY(-2px);
}
```

3. Improve Quiz Option Radio Button Visibility

Add this to make radio buttons more visible on dark background:

```css
.quiz-option input {
  transform: scale(1.1);
  margin-right: 8px;
  accent-color: #f4a261; /* Makes radio buttons visible with accent color */
}
```

4. Fix the Check Answers Button (Optional, for consistency)

Update the .btn-primary to ensure good contrast:

```css
.btn-primary {
  background: var(--primary);
  color: white;
  border: none;
}

.btn-primary:hover {
  background: #1d6a43;
  color: white;
}
```

